{"ts": "2026-07-19T03:35:38.096Z", "seq": 26, "kind": "observation", "summary": "eu7 harness has TWO vacuous-green hazards; any release running eu7 must guard both. (1) THE DOCUMENTED RUN COMMAND DOES NOT WORK. src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:85-86 documents 'AGENT_LONG=1 cargo test -p fathomdb-engine --features default-embedder --test eu7_real_corpus_ac'. That fails with EXIT 101: 'target eu7_real_corpus_ac in package fathomdb-engine requires the features: operator'. Working invocation: --features default-embedder,operator. Fix the docstring (0.8.20 Slice 5 owns it). (2) THE CORPUS IS UNREACHABLE FROM A LINKED WORKTREE. data/corpus-data/ is gitignored (.gitignore:9) and exists ONLY in the primary checkout (2.1 GB). From a worktree, load_subset_or_skip finds nothing, the test prints [skip] and returns EXIT 0 -- a full vacuous green having measured nothing. Workaround used at 0.8.20 Slice-0: symlink data/corpus-data from the primary checkout into the worktree and exclude it via .git/info/exclude (no tracked file changes). GUARD REQUIRED: assert a NON-SKIP WITNESS (e.g. the EU7_SETUP real_docs=N line) rather than trusting exit 0. Compounded by the known trap background-exit-masks-real-exit: a trailing echo around the cargo invocation reported exit 0 while the real exit was 101 -- this recurred live during Slice-0.", "cx": "TC-13", "release": "0.8.20", "slice": "0", "status": "OPEN", "refs": ["file:src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs", "file:dev/plans/runs/STATUS-0.8.20.md#6.2"]}
